solution:
For bcc structure
$$
d=\frac{\sqrt{3} a}{2}
$$
where $d=$ distance between two atoms $a=$ edge length
$$
\begin{aligned}
& 1.73=\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} a \\
& a=\frac{2 \times 1.73}{\sqrt{3}}=2 Å=200 \mathrm{pm}
\end{aligned}
$$

For an ionic substance in FCC arrangement,
$$
\begin{aligned}
& 2\left(r^{+}+r^{-}\right)=\text {edge length } \\
& 2\left(110+r^{-}\right)=508 \\
& r^{-}=144 \mathrm{pm}
\end{aligned}
$$
